The paper discusses the use of neural networks and Gaussian processes for function approximation and solving partial differential equations, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of analytical formulas and hyperparameter optimization, which are techniques often used in the statistical inference (cs.SI) sub-category.
